# from torchvision import datasets, transforms
import torchvision
from torch.utils.data import DataLoader, Subset
from torchvision.datasets import ImageFolder
from torchvision.transforms import ToPILImage, Compose, ToTensor, Resize, Normalize, RandomHorizontalFlip, RandomVerticalFlip, CenterCrop, ColorJitter
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from pathlib import Path


# sample is % of data to use
# get loaders function is used to extract the training and test data from the sub-folders
# we also define the validation loader
def get_loaders(sample=1, normalize=True, horizontal_flip=True, vertical_flip=True, center_crop=True):
    DIR = "/Users/princessspotty/Desktop/Coursework N.C./Zohra Bouchamaoui - 150000533 - NC Coursework/pythonProject/dog vs cat/dataset/"
    DIR_TRAIN = DIR + "training_set"
    DIR_TEST = DIR + "test_set"
    trans = [Resize((128, 128)), ToTensor()]

    if normalize:
        trans.append(Normalize(0.5, 0.5, 0.5))
    if horizontal_flip:
        trans.append(RandomHorizontalFlip(p=0.5))
    if vertical_flip:
        trans.append(RandomVerticalFlip(p=0.5))
    if center_crop:
        trans.append(CenterCrop(224))
    train_folder = ImageFolder(DIR_TRAIN, transform=Compose(trans))
    print("Original train ", len(train_folder))
    sample_ids = list(range(0, len(train_folder), int(1.0 / sample)))
    sampled_train = Subset(train_folder, sample_ids)

    test_folder = ImageFolder(DIR_TEST, transform=Compose(trans))
    test_loader = DataLoader(test_folder, batch_size=128)

    train_idx, valid_idx = train_test_split(list(range(len(sampled_train))), test_size=0.2)

    train_dataset = Subset(sampled_train, train_idx)
    valid_dataset = Subset(sampled_train, valid_idx)

    train_loader = DataLoader(train_dataset, batch_size=128)
    valid_loader = DataLoader(valid_dataset, batch_size=128)

    return train_loader, valid_loader, test_loader


def plot_sample(train_loader):
    tim, lbl = next(iter(train_loader))
    # img = tim[0].reshape(tim[0].shape[1], tim[0].shape[2], tim[0].shape[0])
    catId = list(lbl).index(0)
    dogId = list(lbl).index(1)
    cat = ToPILImage()(tim[catId]).convert("RGB")
    dog = ToPILImage()(tim[dogId]).convert("RGB")
    # helper.imshow(tim[0])

    plt.imshow(cat)
    plt.show()
    plt.imshow(dog)
    plt.show()


if __name__ == "__main__":
    # prints images without changes
    train_loader, _, _ = get_loaders(sample=0.01, normalize=False, horizontal_flip=False, vertical_flip=False, center_crop=False)
    plot_sample(train_loader)

    # prints images after performing data augmentation
    train_loader_change, _, _ = get_loaders(sample=0.01, normalize=True, horizontal_flip=False, vertical_flip=False, center_crop=False)
    plot_sample(train_loader_change)
    
    train_loader_change, _, _ = get_loaders(sample=0.01, normalize=True, horizontal_flip=True, vertical_flip=False, center_crop=False)
    plot_sample(train_loader_change)
    
    train_loader_change, _, _ = get_loaders(sample=0.01, normalize=True, horizontal_flip=False, vertical_flip=True, center_crop=False)
    plot_sample(train_loader_change)
    
    train_loader_change, _, _ = get_loaders(sample=0.01, normalize=True, horizontal_flip=False, vertical_flip=False, center_crop=True)
    plot_sample(train_loader_change)
